# gen46: additional-class assertion. Explanatory prose adds memberships
# incrementally -- "a dolphin is also a mammal". "<x> is also a/an <y>" asserts
# y(x), the same membership as "x is a y" with one extra class. A small step
# growing the extractor toward real prose (the bench's wall is open-domain
# language; this is one honest shape closer).
> flipper is a dolphin
< Learned: dolphin(flipper).
> flipper is also a mammal
< Learned: mammal(flipper).
# Both memberships now hold.
> is flipper a mammal?
< Yes.
> is flipper a dolphin?
< Yes.
